    <h1>Jailhouse driver</h1>
    <ul id="toc"></ul>
    <p>
        The libvirt Jailhouse driver provides rudimentary support for managing Jailhouse cells.
    </p>


    <h2><a name="project">Project Links</a></h2>
    <ul>
      <li>
        The <a href="https://github.com/siemens/jailhouse">Jailhouse</a> project.
      </li>
    </ul>


    <h2><a name="uri">Connections to the Jailhouse driver</a></h2>
    <p>
        The Jailhouse driver utilizes the Jailhouse binary to provide management of cells using libvirt. The binary must be in $PATH for the driver to use it. Those connection URIs should suffice:
    </p>
<pre>
jailhouse:///                       (local access)
jailhouse+ssh://root@example.com/   (remote access, SSH tunnelled)
</pre>

